CSS ->

    Cascading Style Sheet
    It is used to style our web page
    It is not a case sensitive
    Line by line execution

    v3



    p -> property
    v -> value
    rel -> relation

    Types ->
        1. Inline
            In This css we put a style attribute on any tag

            Example ->

            <tag style="p:v;......"></tag>
      
        2. Internal
            Here we write our styles inside head tag using style tag

            Example ->
            <head>
                <style>
                    selector{
                        p:v;
                        ..
                    }
                    ..
                    ..
                </style>
            </head>


        3. External (.css)
            here we create a file with extension .css
            then we attach that css file with our html using link tag inside head

            Example ->
            first.css
             selector{
                 p:v;
                ..
            }
                    ..
                    ..


    first.html


    <head>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="filename.css">
    </head>



    selector ->
        1. tagname
        2. classname (.)
        3. id (#)
        4. * (universal selector -> apply on all)









